channel.title: Computer is messed up
channel.description:
Yesterday I went on my other computer, and turn it on like I usually do. Then there comes a error message saying that "Windows didn't start correctly..." there's more but I can't remember all, then there's 4 options below. 1) Start in safe mode 2) Start safe modes command line 3) Start in safe mode and run command line 4) Run windows with the latest settings (using the settings that worked before this error). I tried all of them, it just shows me the normal windows startup and then reboots. I tried to format by holding F10 and it won't let me format it either. I didn't do anything, just shut it down normally before I went on it again and now it's like this.
Note: I have two computers.
